  "texts": [
    "In their study, Bran et al.",
    "found that four analysed news sources presented conflicting narratives about Chat-GPT's competence as a social actor, with some depicting it as creative and healing, offering valuable novelty, companionship the need for social acceptance [36].",
    "Conversely, some sources portrayed AI as incompetent, polluting human culture, and replacing human skills and knowledge with stochastic, illusionary competence or even imposture.",
    "This dual representation leads to a contested social agency, vacillating between creative actors and essentially unthinking tools.Additionally, Shijie et al.",
    "underscored the importance of evaluating the credibility of AI-generated content by considering AI's role as a content generator and technological medium [37]."
  ],
